Package: climatelink
Title: Link Biological Observations to Climate Exposure Windows
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Heat Centre", "Climate Data Toolkit", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "noreply@example.org")
Description: Attach ERA5-Land climate exposure windows to biological or point
    data that carry a location and a timestamp. For every observation the package
    summarises climate variables (temperature, precipitation, humidity, wind,
    solar radiation, pressure, evapotranspiration) over the N days leading up to
    the observation date, using mean/max/min/sum aggregations. It wraps the Python
    'Climate_API' extractor via 'reticulate' and Google Earth Engine, giving R
    users a native data.frame-in / data.frame-out workflow.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.28)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
